      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "aa3b78ec-de6c-4ff9-8b3b-037b34a92bff",
          "content": "The code compiles. Let me show you a summary of the changes made:\n\n**Summary of changes to `/local/home/patwie/git/github.com/patwie/drafft-ink/crates/drafftink-app/src/event_handler.rs`:**\n\n1. Added `ShapeTrait` to imports to access `bounds()` method\n\n2. Added new field to `EventHandler` struct:\n   ```rust\n   text_edit_original_center: Option<Point>\n   ```\n\n3. Modified `enter_text_edit()` to store the original center:\n   ```rust\n   self.text_edit_original_center = canvas.document.get_shape(id)\n       .map(|shape| shape.bounds().center());\n   ```\n\n4. Modified `exit_text_edit()` to preserve visual center:\n   ```rust\n   if let Some(original_center) = self.text_edit_original_center {\n       if let Some(Shape::Text(text)) = canvas.document.get_shape_mut(id) {\n           let new_center = text.bounds().center();\n           let offset = original_center - new_center;\n           text.position.x += offset.x;\n           text.position.y += offset.y;\n       }\n   }\n   // ...\n   self.text_edit_original_center = None;\n   ```\n\nThis ensures that when you edit rotated text and the content grows or shrinks, the text's visual center stays in the same place. The position (top-left) is adjusted by the difference between the original center and the new center after editing."
        }
      },
