        "Response": {
          "message_id": "a2810298-e403-4637-b42a-f496b6412225",
          "content": "Done. Now the code:\n\n1. On entering text edit: stores the **rotated top-left** position (the visual top-left corner after rotation is applied)\n2. On exiting text edit: computes the new rotated top-left and adjusts `text.position` so the rotated top-left stays in the same place\n\nThis means:\n- The visual top-left corner stays fixed when text content changes\n- Rotation still happens around the center (as before)\n- Non-rotated text behaves the same as before (top-left stays put)"
        }
      },
