          "message_id": "c63dc333-c1d6-4d38-8514-67cc960d9658",
          "content": "Now I understand! The rotation is applied around the **center** of the bounds. So when text content changes:\n1. The bounds change (width/height)\n2. The center changes\n3. The rotation pivot changes\n4. The visual position shifts\n\nThe fix should preserve the **rotated top-left corner** position. Let me trace through the math:\n\n- Before edit: center_old, rotation around center_old, top-left at position_old\n- After edit: center_new (different because bounds changed), rotation around center_new\n\nWe need to find the new `position` such that the rotated top-left stays the same.",
