      "assistant": {
        "ToolUse": {
          "message_id": "c59214a0-4bd5-4835-b12e-6336891ab1f1",
          "content": "Yes! The issue is that `bounds()` uses `cached_size` which is set by the renderer. During editing, parley computes the actual size. But when we call `bounds()` in `exit_text_edit`, the cache might have stale data or the text content changed.\n\nLet me invalidate the cache and force a re-render before computing the new position. Actually, the simpler fix is to not rely on bounds at all - just store the width/height at enter time too:",
          "tool_uses": [
            {
              "id": "tooluse_yph_iWFjRH6muEevX3nMIw",
              "name": "fs_read",
              "orig_name": "fs_read",
