          "message_id": "9b5ba9ce-e5cd-43f0-a99e-3659930c89fa",
          "content": "Actually, the simplest fix: invalidate the cache when content changes, so bounds() uses the approximate size consistently. But that's not accurate either.\n\nBetter approach: store the original position and rotation, then after editing compute what position would give the same rotated top-left with the NEW bounds:",
