          "message_id": "648fca07-8b66-4f9b-9c3b-be63558efcbc",
          "content": "Now the issue is that `get_handles` uses `shape.bounds()` which returns different sizes. The problem is the cached size from parley during editing vs approximate/stale after. \n\nThe key insight: we're back to the offset approach, but the offset will be wrong because `get_handles` computes handle position from `bounds()` which changes.\n\nThe fix should be: after adjusting position, the handle position changes again. We need to iterate or solve directly. But since position change = handle change by same amount (for non-rotated), and for rotated it's more complex...\n\nActually wait - when we add offset to position, the center moves by the same offset, so the handle also moves by the same offset. So the offset approach should work! Let me check if there's something else going on.",
          "tool_uses": [
