          "content": "The cached size should persist. But after exit, when the text is rendered normally (not in edit mode), it goes through `render_text` which sets the cached size again. But if the content changed, the new layout might be slightly different.\n\nWait - looking at the log again:\n- First edit (no rotation): size=(55.0, 24.0) for \"Enter\"\n- Second edit (with rotation -0.501): size=(45.6, 24.0) \n\nThe size changed from 55 to 45.6! That's the problem - the size at exit is different from what will be used after.\n\nThe text content is \"Enter\" both times, but the size differs. This might be because during editing, parley computes one size, but after exit when `render_text` runs again, it computes a different size.\n\nLet me check if `set_content` invalidates the cache:",
