        "ToolUse": {
          "message_id": "ff2d2bba-8829-4eb8-a4d6-8b808168d943",
          "content": "Good, the code already has `text.set_cached_size(width, height)` to force the cache. But the issue is that `bounds()` at exit time uses the **editing** cached size, but after exit, `render_text` will compute a **new** layout with potentially different size.\n\nThe real problem: the size computed by `render_text_editing` (parley editor) differs from `render_text` (parley layout builder).\n\nLet me check if we can just skip the position adjustment entirely and see what happens - maybe the issue is elsewhere:",
