      "assistant": {
        "ToolUse": {
          "message_id": "feb1d33e-283e-400e-a380-ef50b980c9ab",
          "content": "Yes! Look at the last line:\n- content='EnterNew' but size=(45.6, 24.0) - same size as 'Enter' alone!\n\nThe cached size isn't being updated when content changes during editing. The `bounds()` is returning stale cached size.\n\nThe issue: during editing, `render_text_editing` uses parley's editor which computes layout, but it doesn't call `text.set_cached_size()`. So `bounds()` returns the old cached size.\n\nLet me check `render_text_editing`:",
          "tool_uses": [
            {
              "id": "tooluse_XCmLmskjShKrDbK1ifM9zw",
              "name": "execute_bash",
              "orig_name": "execute_bash",
              "args": {
                "command": "grep -n \"set_cached_size\" /local/home/patwie/git/github.com/patwie/drafft-ink/crates/drafftink-render/src/vello_impl.rs",
                "summary": "Check if set_cached_size is called in render"
              },
              "orig_args": {
                "command": "grep -n \"set_cached_size\" /local/home/patwie/git/github.com/patwie/drafft-ink/crates/drafftink-render/src/vello_impl.rs",
                "summary": "Check if set_cached_size is called in render"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
