      "assistant": {
        "ToolUse": {
          "message_id": "a1836d29-521a-4a7e-a791-9d42cd2471ff",
          "content": "Wait, that still won't fix it - the center still depends on position + size, so when size changes, center changes, and the rotated text shifts.\n\nThe real fix: we need to adjust `text.position` so that the **rotated top-left** stays fixed when size changes. But we can't modify `text` in the renderer (it's borrowed).\n\nLet me think differently: instead of adjusting position, compute the transform to render at the correct location regardless of what `text.position` says. We need to render such that the top-left handle stays at the anchor.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: in the renderer, compute where the text SHOULD be rendered to keep anchor fixed, and use that for the transform instead of `text.position`.\n\nBut we need access to the anchor. Let me pass it to `render_text_editing`:",
          "tool_uses": [
            {
              "id": "tooluse_FRZ2JGmKRGK4NdF6Gd0xHw",
              "name": "execute_bash",
              "orig_name": "execute_bash",
              "args": {
                "command": "grep -n \"render_text_editing\" /local/home/patwie/git/github.com/patwie/drafft-ink/crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs",
                "summary": "Find where render_text_editing is called"
              },
              "orig_args": {
                "command": "grep -n \"render_text_editing\" /local/home/patwie/git/github.com/patwie/drafft-ink/crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs",
                "summary": "Find where render_text_editing is called"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
