  "transcript": [
    "> lets use Ctrl+A to select all elements. And implement a way we can easily list/document all short cuts automatically",
    "I'll implement Ctrl+A to select all elements and create a shortcut registry system. Let me start by examining the current code structure.\n[Tool uses: fs_read,fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Now let me check the keyboard shortcut handling in app.rs:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Perfect! Now I can see the structure. Let me check if there are all shapes available:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Now let me check the document structure to see how to get all shape IDs:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me implement:\n1. A `select_all()` method in canvas.rs\n2. Add Ctrl+A handler in app.rs\n3. Create a shortcut registry system\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "> t",
    "Now let's add the Ctrl+A handler in app.rs:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "Now let's create a shortcut registry system. I'll create a new module for this:\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "Now let's add the shortcuts module to lib.rs:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "Now let's add a way to display shortcuts in the UI. Let me check the UI code:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Now let's add a \"Keyboard Shortcuts\" menu item that shows all shortcuts. First, let me check the UiAction enum:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Let me add a ShowShortcuts action and update the UI state to track if shortcuts modal is open:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Now let me add the ShowShortcuts action and update the UI state:\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "Now add a field to UiState to track if shortcuts modal is open:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
