    "Excellent! Everything compiles successfully. Let me create a summary:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented **Shift+Drag aspect ratio preservation** for all shape resizing operations in Drafft.ink.\n\n### What Was Implemented ✅\n\n**Shift+Drag Aspect Ratio Preservation:**\n- When resizing any shape using corner handles, holding **Shift** now maintains the original aspect ratio\n- Works for all shape types:\n  - Rectangle\n  - Ellipse  \n  - Freehand drawings\n  - Images\n  - Text\n  - Groups\n\n### Technical Implementation\n\n1. **Updated `apply_manipulation()` function** in `selection.rs`:\n   - Added `keep_aspect_ratio: bool` parameter\n   - Passes this flag to all resize functions\n\n2. **Modified all resize functions** to support aspect ratio:\n   - `apply_corner_resize_rect()`\n   - `apply_corner_resize_ellipse()`\n   - `apply_corner_resize_freehand()`\n   - `apply_corner_resize_image()`\n   \n3. **Aspect ratio logic**:\n   - Calculates original aspect ratio from bounds\n   - Uses the larger dimension change (width or height)\n   - Applies uniform scaling to maintain proportions\n   - For freehand: scales all points uniformly\n\n4. **Event handler integration**:\n   - Changed `_input` to `input` parameter in `handle_drag()`\n   - Passes `input.modifiers.shift` to `apply_manipulation()` calls\n   - Works in both preview (during drag) and finalize (on release)\n\n### Files Modified:\n- `crates/drafftink-core/src/selection.rs` - Core resize logic\n- `crates/drafftink-app/src/event_handler.rs` - Shift modifier detection\n- `crates/drafftink-app/src/shortcuts.rs` - Documentation\n\n### Tests Added:\n- `test_aspect_ratio_resize()` - Verifies aspect ratio is maintained with Shift\n\nAll code compiles successfully and all 8 tests pass! The implementation is minimal, clean, and follows the existing codebase patterns.\n[Tool uses: none]",
