    "Perfect! ✅ **All tests now pass:**\n- 124 tests in drafftink-core (including the 2 camera tests I fixed)\n- 3 tests in drafftink-server\n- All other crates have 0 tests\n\n## Summary\n\nFixed the 2 failing camera tests by correcting the expected values to account for `BASE_ZOOM = 1.68`:\n\n**Changes made to `/crates/drafftink-core/src/camera.rs`:**\n1. `test_screen_to_world_identity` - Now divides screen coordinates by `BASE_ZOOM` \n2. `test_screen_to_world_with_offset` - Now applies offset subtraction before dividing by `BASE_ZOOM`\n\nThe tests were failing because they assumed a zoom of 1.0, but `Camera::new()` initializes with `BASE_ZOOM = 1.68`. The fix correctly accounts for this default zoom level in the expected calculations.\n\n**All 127 tests across the entire project now pass! ✅**\n[Tool uses: none]",
