    "Excellent! Let me create a summary document:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented a local storage system with \"Save Local\", \"Save Local As\", and \"Open Recent\" functionality:\n\n### Changes Made ✅\n\n**1. UI State Updates (`ui.rs`):**\n- Added `save_dialog_open`, `open_dialog_open` fields to track modal states\n- Added `save_name_input` for document name input\n- Added `recent_documents` Vec to track recently saved documents\n\n**2. New UI Actions:**\n- `SaveLocal` - Save with current document name (Ctrl+S)\n- `SaveLocalAs` - Show dialog to rename and save\n- `ShowOpenDialog` - Show recent documents dialog\n- `SaveLocalWithName(String)` - Save with specified name\n- `LoadLocal(String)` - Load document by name\n\n**3. Updated File Menu:**\n- \"Save Local\" (Ctrl+S) - Quick save with current name\n- \"Save Local As...\" - Rename and save\n- \"Open\" section with:\n  - \"Open Recent\" - Shows list of saved documents\n  - \"Open...\" (Ctrl+O) - File picker dialog\n\n**4. Modal Dialogs:**\n- **Save Dialog**: Text input for document name with Save/Cancel buttons\n- **Open Dialog**: Scrollable list of recent documents (up to 10)\n\n**5. File Operations:**\n- **Native**: Added `load_document_by_name()` (uses file picker)\n- **WASM**: Added `load_document_by_name_async()` and `list_documents_async()` for IndexedDB\n\n**6. Implementation Details:**\n- Documents saved with name as ID in IndexedDB (WASM)\n- Recent documents list maintained (max 10)\n- Modals have backdrop click-to-close\n- Enter key submits save dialog\n\n**Files Modified:**\n- `crates/drafftink-app/src/ui.rs` - UI state, actions, menu, modals\n- `crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs` - Action handlers, file operations\n- `crates/drafftink-app/src/shortcuts.rs` - Updated shortcuts\n\nAll code compiles successfully! The system now provides a clean local storage workflow with document naming and recent document access.\n[Tool uses: none]",
