    "Perfect! ✅ Now let me create a summary:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've implemented IndexedDB integration to populate the recent documents list:\n\n### Changes Made ✅\n\n**1. WASM File Operations (`app.rs`):**\n- Added `PENDING_DOCUMENT_LIST` thread-local storage\n- Updated `list_documents_async()` to store results in thread-local\n- Added `take_pending_document_list()` to retrieve the list\n- Filters out `\"__last__\"` system document\n\n**2. Dialog Handlers:**\n- `ShowOpenDialog` - Triggers `list_documents_async()` when opened\n- `ShowOpenRecentDialog` - Triggers `list_documents_async()` when opened\n\n**3. Frame Update:**\n- Added check for `take_pending_document_list()` on each frame\n- Updates `ui_state.recent_documents` when list arrives\n- Works asynchronously without blocking UI\n\n### How It Works:\n\n1. User clicks \"Open\" or \"Open Recent...\"\n2. Handler calls `file_ops::list_documents_async()`\n3. Async task queries IndexedDB for all document IDs\n4. Results stored in `PENDING_DOCUMENT_LIST`\n5. Next frame checks and updates `ui_state.recent_documents`\n6. Dialog shows the actual saved documents\n\nAll code compiles successfully! The recent documents list now properly loads from IndexedDB on WASM.\n[Tool uses: none]",
