    "The refactoring is complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary\n\n### 1. Updated Dependencies (`drafftink-core/Cargo.toml`)\n- Added `winit.workspace = true`\n- Added `winit_input_helper = \"0.17\"`\n\n### 2. Refactored `InputState` (`drafftink-core/src/input.rs`)\n- Replaced manual tracking with `WinitInputHelper`\n- Removed old enums: `PointerEvent`, `KeyEvent`, `MouseButton`, `Modifiers`\n- Now uses winit types directly (`winit::event::MouseButton`, `winit::keyboard::KeyCode`)\n- New API methods:\n  - `step()` / `end_step()` - frame lifecycle\n  - `process_window_event()` / `process_device_event()` - event processing\n  - `mouse_position()`, `is_button_pressed()`, `mouse_just_pressed()`, `mouse_just_released()`\n  - `scroll_delta()`, `cursor_diff()`\n  - `is_key_pressed()`, `is_key_just_pressed()`, `is_key_just_released()`\n  - `shift()`, `ctrl()`, `alt()` - modifier queries\n  - Retained custom double-click detection and drag tracking\n\n### 3. Updated Event Loop (`drafftink-app/src/app.rs`)\n- Added `state.input.process_window_event(&event)` call\n- Added `new_events()` handler calling `input.step()`\n- Added `about_to_wait()` handler calling `input.end_step()`\n- Removed manual `PointerEvent`/`KeyEvent` construction\n- Updated all modifier checks to use new methods (`shift()`, `ctrl()`, `alt()`)\n- Updated `pointer_position` to `mouse_position()`\n- Updated `pointer_delta()` to `cursor_diff()`\n\n### 4. Fixed Call Sites (`drafftink-app/src/event_handler.rs`)\n- Changed `input.modifiers.shift` → `input.shift()`\n- Changed `input.modifiers.alt` → `input.alt()`\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> lets fix these warnings (Iam worried that PngRenderResult is unused, really? We have export as png)> \n> \n   Compiling drafftink-app v0.1.0 (/local/home/patwie/git/github.com/patwie/drafft-ink/crates/drafftink-app)> \nwarning: unused import: `PngRenderResult`> \n  --> crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs:11:50> \n   |> \n11 | use drafftink_render::{AngleSnapInfo, GridStyle, PngRenderResult, RenderContext, Renderer, TextEditResult, TextEditState, TextKey, TextModifiers, VelloRenderer};> \n   |                                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^> \n   |> \n   = note: `#[warn(unused_imports)]` (part of `#[warn(unused)]`) on by default> \n> \nwarning: unused import: `winit::dpi::LogicalSize`> \n  --> crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs:17:5> \n   |> \n17 | use winit::dpi::LogicalSize;> \n   |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^> \n> \nwarning: use of deprecated method `egui::Context::screen_rect`: screen_rect has been split into viewport_rect() and content_rect(). You likely should use content_rect()> \n    --> crates/drafftink-app/src/ui.rs:1793:35> \n     |> \n1793 |             let screen_rect = ctx.screen_rect();> \n     |                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^> \n     |> \n     = note: `#[warn(deprecated)]` on by default> \n> \nwarning: use of deprecated method `egui::Context::screen_rect`: screen_rect has been split into viewport_rect() and content_rect(). You likely should use content_rect()> \n    --> crates/drafftink-app/src/ui.rs:1858:35> \n     |> \n1858 |             let screen_rect = ctx.screen_rect();> \n     |                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^> \n> \nwarning: use of deprecated method `egui::Context::screen_rect`: screen_rect has been split into viewport_rect() and content_rect(). You likely should use content_rect()> \n    --> crates/drafftink-app/src/ui.rs:1927:35> \n     |> \n1927 |             let screen_rect = ctx.screen_rect();> \n     |                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^> \n> \nwarning: use of deprecated method `egui::Context::screen_rect`: screen_rect has been split into viewport_rect() and content_rect(). You likely should use content_rect()> \n    --> crates/drafftink-app/src/ui.rs:1991:35> \n     |> \n1991 |             let screen_rect = ctx.screen_rect();> \n     |                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^> \n> \nwarning: unused variable: `render_cx`> \n    --> crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs:1476:13> \n     |> \n1476 |         let render_cx = self> \n     |             ^^^^^^^^^ help: if this is intentional, prefix it with an underscore: `_render_cx`> \n     |> \n",
