    "> /model",
    "> Here is a detailed plan to refactor your IndexedDB implementation using `rexie`, including a self-contained example.> \n> \n### 1\\. Dependency Updates> \n> \nFirst, you need to update `crates/drafftink-core/Cargo.toml` to include `rexie`. You should also include `serde-wasm-bindgen` to handle the conversion between Rust structs and JavaScript values stored in IDB.> \n> \n**File:** `crates/drafftink-core/Cargo.toml`> \n> \n```toml> \n[dependencies]> \n# ... existing dependencies> \nrexie = \"0.6\"> \nserde-wasm-bindgen = \"0.6\" > \n```> \n> \n### 2\\. Implementation Plan> \n> \nThe goal is to replace the raw `web-sys` logic with `rexie`'s high-level abstractions.> \n> \n1.  **Change Struct Definition:** Replace the `Rc<RefCell<Option<IdbDatabase>>>` with a structure that holds the `Rexie` instance. `Rexie` is not `Clone` by default, so you might need to keep it wrapped in `Rc` or `OnceCell`.> \n2.  **Simplify Initialization:** `rexie` handles the `onupgradeneeded` logic declaratively. You define the object stores in the builder, and it handles the versioning.> \n3.  **Refactor CRUD Operations:**> \n      * **Save:** Serialize your `CanvasDocument` using `serde_wasm_bindgen` before passing it to `store.put()`.> \n      * **Load:** Retrieve the `JsValue` and deserialize it back using `serde_wasm_bindgen`.> \n> \n### 3\\. Self-Contained Example> \n> \nHere is a complete, runnable example snippet showing how the new implementation will look.> \n> \n```rust> \nuse rexie::{Rexie, TransactionMode, ObjectStore};> \nuse serde::{Serialize, Deserialize};> \nuse wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;> \n> \n#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize, Debug)]> \nstruct UserDoc {> \n    id: String,> \n    content: String,> \n}> \n> \npub async fn run_rexie_example() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {> \n    // 1. Build the Database> \n    // Rexie handles versioning and store creation automatically.> \n    let db = Rexie::builder(\"drafftink_db\")> \n        .version(1)> \n        .add_object_store(ObjectStore::new(\"documents\"))> \n        .build()> \n        .await?;> \n> \n    // 2. Write Data (Save)> \n    // We need a ReadWrite transaction> \n    let transaction = db.transaction(&[\"documents\"], TransactionMode::ReadWrite)?;> \n    let store = transaction.store(\"documents\")?;> \n> \n    let doc = UserDoc { > \n        id: \"doc-1\".to_string(), > \n        content: \"Hello World\".to_string() > \n    };> \n> \n    // Convert Rust struct to JsValue for storage> \n    let js_value = serde_wasm_bindgen::to_value(&doc)?;> \n    let js_key = JsValue::from_str(&doc.id);> \n> \n    // .put(value, key) - key is optional if using in-line keys, > \n    // but here we use the doc ID explicitly> \n    store.put(&js_value, Some(&js_key)).await?;> \n    > \n    // Explicitly wait for transaction to complete (optional but good practice)> \n    transaction.done().await?;> \n> \n    // 3. Read Data (Load)> \n    let transaction = db.transaction(&[\"documents\"], TransactionMode::ReadOnly)?;> \n    let store = transaction.store(\"documents\")?;> \n> \n    let js_doc = store.get(&js_key).await?; // Returns JsValue> \n    let loaded_doc: UserDoc = serde_wasm_bindgen::from_value(js_doc)?;> \n> \n    println!(\"Loaded document: {:?}\", loaded_doc);> \n> \n    Ok(())> \n}> \n```> \n> \n### 4\\. Refactoring `crates/drafftink-core/src/storage/indexeddb.rs`> \n> \nHere is how the core logic in your actual file should change:> \n> \n```rust> \n// In crates/drafftink-core/src/storage/indexeddb.rs> \n> \nuse rexie::{Rexie, TransactionMode, ObjectStore};> \n> \nimpl IndexedDbStorage {> \n    // Replace the raw initialization with this> \n    async fn get_db(&self) -> StorageResult<Rexie> {> \n        // ... (cache check logic) ...> \n> \n        let rexie = Rexie::builder(\"drafftink\")> \n            .version(1)> \n            .add_object_store(ObjectStore::new(\"documents\"))> \n            .build()> \n            .await> \n            .map_err(|e| StorageError::Other(e.to_string()))?;> \n> \n        // ... (cache set logic) ...> \n        Ok(rexie)> \n    }> \n}> \n> \n// Example: Refactored save method> \nfn save(&self, id: &str, document: &CanvasDocument) -> BoxFuture<'_, StorageResult<()>> {> \n    let id = id.to_string();> \n    let doc_clone = document.clone(); // Clone usually needed for async move> \n> \n    Box::pin(async move {> \n        let db = self.get_db().await?;> \n        let transaction = db.transaction(&[\"documents\"], TransactionMode::ReadWrite)> \n            .map_err(|e| StorageError::Other(e.to_string()))?;> \n        > \n        let store = transaction.store(\"documents\")> \n            .map_err(|e| StorageError::Other(e.to_string()))?;> \n            > \n        // Use serde-wasm-bindgen for better performance than JSON string> \n        let js_val = serde_wasm_bindgen::to_value(&doc_clone)> \n            .map_err(|e| StorageError::Serialization(e.to_string()))?;> \n            > \n        store.put(&js_val, Some(&wasm_bindgen::JsValue::from_str(&id)))> \n            .await> \n            .map_err(|e| StorageError::Other(e.to_string()))?;> \n            > \n        transaction.done().await.map_err(|e| StorageError::Other(e.to_string()))?;> \n        Ok(())> \n    })> \n}> \n```",
