    "Excellent! The refactoring is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## IndexedDB Refactoring Summary\n\n### 1. **Dependencies Updated**\n- Added `rexie = \"0.6\"` for high-level IndexedDB abstraction\n- Added `serde-wasm-bindgen = \"0.6\"` for efficient Rust ↔ JS serialization\n\n### 2. **Code Simplification**\n- **Before**: 200+ lines of complex web-sys IndexedDB code with manual Promise handling\n- **After**: ~100 lines of clean, readable rexie code\n\n### 3. **Key Improvements**\n- **Declarative DB setup**: `Rexie::builder()` handles versioning and store creation automatically\n- **Better serialization**: `serde-wasm-bindgen` instead of JSON strings for better performance\n- **Cleaner async**: No more manual Promise/Closure handling\n- **Simplified error handling**: Consistent error mapping throughout\n- **Removed caching complexity**: Rexie is lightweight enough to recreate connections\n\n### 4. **API Compatibility**\n- All `Storage` trait methods work exactly the same\n- No changes needed in calling code\n- Same error types and behavior\n\nThe new implementation is much more maintainable and follows modern Rust WASM patterns using `rexie`'s high-level abstractions instead of raw `web-sys` calls.\n[Tool uses: none]",
