    "Both builds compile successfully. The only remaining warning is about an unused function in web.rs which is unrelated to our changes.\n\nHere's a summary of the changes made to add copy/paste support for text objects:\n\n**Changes to `drafftink-render/src/text_editor.rs`:**\n1. Added `Copy`, `Cut`, and `Paste(String)` variants to the `TextKey` enum\n2. Added `Copy(String)` variant to `TextEditResult` to return selected text for clipboard operations\n3. Implemented handling for these new keys in `handle_key()`:\n   - `Copy`: Returns the selected text via `TextEditResult::Copy`\n   - `Cut`: Returns selected text and deletes it from the editor\n   - `Paste`: Inserts the provided text at cursor/replaces selection\n\n**Changes to `drafftink-app/src/app.rs`:**\n1. Added detection for Ctrl+C/X/V during text editing mode\n2. Maps Ctrl+C to `TextKey::Copy`, Ctrl+X to `TextKey::Cut`\n3. For Ctrl+V, reads text from clipboard (via arboard on native) and creates `TextKey::Paste(text)`\n4. Handles `TextEditResult::Copy` by writing the returned text to the system clipboard\n5. Proper `#[cfg]` guards ensure arboard is only used on native builds\n[Tool uses: none]",
