    "Both builds compile successfully. The implementation is complete.\n\nHere's a summary of the WASM clipboard support added:\n\n**Changes to `drafftink-app/src/app.rs` (WASM file_ops module):**\n1. Added `PENDING_CLIPBOARD_TEXT` thread-local storage for async clipboard results\n2. Added `request_clipboard_text()` - spawns async task to read clipboard text\n3. Added `take_pending_clipboard_text()` - retrieves pending clipboard text if available\n4. Added `read_clipboard_text_async()` - async helper using browser Clipboard API\n5. Added `copy_text_to_clipboard()` - fire-and-forget async clipboard write\n\n**Changes to keyboard handling:**\n1. On Ctrl+V in WASM: calls `request_clipboard_text()` to start async read, returns None immediately\n2. At start of text editing key handling: checks for `take_pending_clipboard_text()` and processes it as a paste\n3. On `TextEditResult::Copy` in WASM: calls `copy_text_to_clipboard()` instead of the placeholder\n\nThe paste has a one-frame delay in WASM due to the async nature of the browser Clipboard API, but this is imperceptible to users.\n[Tool uses: none]",
