    "Done! Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Added `reconstruct()` methods to all shape types:**\n- `Rectangle::reconstruct(id, position, width, height, corner_radius, style)`\n- `Ellipse::reconstruct(id, center, radius_x, radius_y, style)`\n- `Line::reconstruct(id, start, end, intermediate_points, path_style, style)`\n- `Arrow::reconstruct(id, start, end, intermediate_points, path_style, head_size, style)`\n- `Freehand::reconstruct(id, points, style)`\n- `Text::reconstruct(id, position, content, font_size, font_family, font_weight, style)`\n- `Group::reconstruct(id, children)` (replaced `with_id`)\n- `Image::reconstruct(id, position, width, height, source_width, source_height, format, data_base64, style)`\n\n**Refactored `convert.rs`:**\n- Removed all `serde_json` usage and the `style_to_json` helper\n- Each `*_from_loro` function now directly calls `Shape::reconstruct()` \n- Added serialization for `intermediate_points` and `path_style` for Line/Arrow (bonus fix - these weren't being persisted before)\n- Added helper `get_id()` and `points_from_loro()` functions to reduce duplication\n\n**Benefits:**\n1. No more JSON serialization/deserialization overhead\n2. Direct struct construction is much faster\n3. Code is cleaner and more explicit about reconstruction intent\n4. `intermediate_points` and `path_style` are now properly persisted for Line/Arrow shapes\n[Tool uses: none]",
