    "Done! Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've implemented the text tool interaction changes:\n\n### Changes Made:\n\n1. **`crates/drafftink-core/src/selection.rs`**:\n   - Added `hit_test_boundary()` function to detect if a point is on the edge of a shape's bounding box (within tolerance)\n\n2. **`crates/drafftink-app/src/event_handler.rs`**:\n   - Modified text tool press handler to check in order:\n     1. Handle hits (corners) → starts scale manipulation\n     2. Boundary hits (edges) → starts move operation\n     3. Interior clicks → enters text edit mode\n   - Added `get_cursor_for_position()` method that returns cursor type based on hover:\n     - `0` = default cursor\n     - `1` = move cursor (hovering over draggable area)\n     - `2` = resize cursor (hovering over scale handles)\n\n3. **`crates/drafftink-app/src/app.rs`**:\n   - Imported `CursorIcon` from winit\n   - Added cursor update logic in `CursorMoved` handler that sets the window cursor based on hover position (only when not dragging)\n\n### Behavior:\n- **Text tool selected + click inside text**: enters edit mode\n- **Text tool selected + click on boundary**: starts dragging the text\n- **Text tool selected + click on corner handle**: starts scaling\n- **Text tool selected + click elsewhere**: creates new text (on release)\n- **Cursor changes**: Move cursor when hovering over draggable areas, resize cursor when hovering over scale handles\n[Tool uses: none]",
