    "> i reverted your last touch pixel delta scroll delta changes . we need to overhaul the entire touch handling. Clicking rectangle, then clicking somewhere and drag somwhere should insert that rectangle. same for other shapes.",
    "I understand - the touch handling needs to work like mouse: tap to start drawing, drag to size the shape, release to finish. Let me look at the current touch implementation and fix it properly.\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "The issue is that `is_single_touch()` returns false during `TouchPhase::Started` because the touch was just added. Let me check the input.rs logic:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "I see the problem. The `process_touch` is called first, which updates the state, then we check `is_single_touch()`. But the logic flow is wrong - we need to handle single touch drawing separately from the gesture detection.\n\nLet me rewrite the touch handling to be cleaner:\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "Now add the `touch_count` method to InputState:\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "Build succeeded. Now touch should work like mouse:\n- **Single finger tap + drag**: Draws shapes (rectangle, ellipse, line, etc.) or selects/moves\n- **Two fingers**: Pinch to zoom, drag to pan\n\nThe key fix was using `touch_count()` after `process_touch()` to check how many fingers are active, rather than checking before the state was updated.\n[Tool uses: none]",
