    "All tests pass. Let me mark the remaining tasks as complete:\n[Tool uses: todo_list]",
    "I've implemented rotation support for shapes and text. Here's a summary of what was added:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### Core Changes (`drafftink-core`)\n\n1. **Added `rotation` field** to `Rectangle`, `Ellipse`, `Text`, and `Image` shapes (in radians, around center)\n\n2. **Added `HandleKind::Rotate`** variant to the selection handle enum\n\n3. **Added rotation methods to `Shape` enum**:\n   - `rotation()` - get rotation angle\n   - `set_rotation()` - set rotation angle\n   - `supports_rotation()` - check if shape supports rotation\n\n4. **Updated `get_handles()`** to include rotation handle for rotatable shapes (positioned above top-center, rotated with the shape)\n\n5. **Added rotation functions**:\n   - `apply_rotation()` - apply rotation to a shape based on cursor position, with optional 15° snapping\n   - `reset_rotation()` - reset rotation to a specific angle\n\n6. **Updated CRDT serialization** to include rotation field\n\n### Rendering Changes (`drafftink-render`)\n\n1. **Rotation handle rendering** - circular handle with arc icon inside\n\n2. **Rotation helper lines** during drag:\n   - Center crosshair\n   - Current angle indicator line\n   - Reference line at 0° (dashed)\n   - Angle arc showing rotation amount\n   - Green color when snapped to 15° increments\n\n3. **Applied rotation transform** when rendering shapes (translate-rotate-translate around center)\n\n### App Changes (`drafftink-app`)\n\n1. **Rotation drag handling** - Shift key snaps to 15° increments\n\n2. **Double-click on rotation handle** resets rotation to 0°\n\n3. **Grab cursor** when hovering over rotation handle\n\n4. **Rotation state tracking** for helper line rendering\n\n### Features\n\n- **Drag rotation handle** to rotate shapes freely\n- **Hold Shift** while dragging to snap to 15° increments (0°, 15°, 30°, 45°, etc.)\n- **Double-click rotation handle** to reset to 0°\n- **Visual feedback** with helper lines showing center, current angle, and reference angle\n- **Handles rotate with shape** - corner handles stay at the rotated corners\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> what else are low hanging fruits to improve drafft",
    "Based on my knowledge of the codebase from our previous work, here are some low-hanging fruit improvements for Drafft.ink:\n\n## Quick Wins\n\n### 1. **Keyboard shortcuts for rotation**\n- `R` key to rotate selected shape by 90°\n- `Shift+R` to rotate by -90°\n- Already have the `set_rotation()` infrastructure\n\n### 2. **Edge handles for resizing**\n- `HandleKind::Edge` exists but isn't implemented\n- Would allow horizontal/vertical-only resizing from edges\n\n### 3. **Flip horizontal/vertical**\n- Simple scale transform with -1 on one axis\n- Common feature in drawing apps\n\n### 4. **Lock aspect ratio by default for images**\n- Images already have `source_width`/`source_height`\n- Just default `keep_aspect_ratio` to true for images\n\n### 5. **Duplicate with offset**\n- Currently Alt+drag duplicates in place\n- Add small offset (10px, 10px) when using Ctrl+D\n\n### 6. **Delete key for selected shapes**\n- Check if Delete/Backspace deletes selection (when not editing text)\n\n### 7. **Escape to deselect all**\n- Quick way to clear selection\n\n### 8. **Arrow keys to nudge shapes**\n- Move selected shapes by 1px (or 10px with Shift)\n- Very common UX pattern\n\n### 9. **Z-order controls**\n- Bring to front / Send to back\n- Move up / Move down one layer\n- Shapes already have order in document\n\n### 10. **Copy/paste style**\n- Copy stroke color, fill, sloppiness from one shape to another\n\n## Which would you like to tackle?\n\nThe easiest ones are probably:\n- **Arrow key nudging** (just translate by delta)\n- **Keyboard rotation shortcuts** (already have `set_rotation`)\n- **Z-order controls** (document already has ordered shapes)\n[Tool uses: none]",
